Around the corner from Cicerone is a nice coffee shop which has much better cappucino than the hotel.	Via Ennio Quirino Visconti 66-68.	Across the street is a quaint pizzaria for a quick meal.	Drink at dinner, not the bar!	Regular buses depart from the front of the hotel or from nearby Piazza Cavour.	Strange and funny, if not slightly annoying.	Likewise we asked for extra blankets because the room was cold twice and never saw them.	Therefore they can gain entry to the rooms and have passcodes to the safe.	Ironically the only thing I wasn't that crazy about was breakfast.	Regardless, I would definitely use this property again.	Tips!!